Product name: Vintage 1960’s Dakin Dream Pets Stuffed Animal Made in Japan for R. Dakin & Company-Purple Cow with Flower-Includes Vintage Kamar gift Box!
Description:
Sweet Dakin Dream Pets Purple Cow with Flower in her mouth, in good previously loved vintage condition. Some light stains on her back.  She He measures 5 inches tall. Included is a vintage 1969 Kamar gift box!
From a Collectors smoke free home
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Dream Pets are collectable miniature stuffed animals, made of velveteen and filled with Willow sawdust, manufactured in Japan beginning in 1957 by Japanese toy designers Tochigi Mongi and Tomy for R. Dakin & Co. The manufacturer surprised Dakin by using these little toys as packing material for a shipment of battery operated toy trains which Dakin had ordered. That same day the president of Dakin, Roger Dakin, placed an order by cable to Japan for 25 dozen of the little velveteen toys, by the end of the day he changed his order to 300 dozen.
By 1961 Dream Pets were being designed by Dakin's senior toy designer Virginia Kemp in the United States. The toys became popular, and by the end of 1979 there were over 2000 different characters. In 1995 Dakin merged with The Applause Toy Co. Applause Toys re-issued copies of 24 of the vintage Dream Pets in 2004.
In late 2005, Dakin ceased to operate as an independent company. The names Dakin and Dream Pets were purchased by retail chain Big Lots, as of July 2011 Big lots had not produced any further Dream pets.

WHO 
needs this wanderlust-ness on her/his wall? Who is almost ready to explore the World, but just needs a little push? Your friend, a loved one or maybe – you?

MAP

Wherever you go becomes a part of you somehow.

your map and embossing tape will be carefully packaged in a separate clear plastic sleeves/foil for protection and will be sent in an original Croatian Post high-quality corrugated cardboard envelope/trapeze shape box. - if you think that some quote from another map would be better you may ask for it. Take your time and check out all the MapsToGo : )

Product name: Vintage Samsonite Carry-On Bag - Samsonite Silhouette Messenger Bag - Choice of Strawberry Red or Tangerine Orange - Vegan Friendly
Description:
Love bags and suitcases? DollFood has more at:
http://www.etsy.com/shop/DollFood/search?search_query=SUITCASE
In excellent vintage condition, this listing is for one (1) gorgeous messenger style bag, likely from the 70s, labeled Samsonite Silhouette, with four handy storage compartments.  You get to choose whether you prefer the strawberry red or tangerine orange shade - both bright and beautiful so you're sure to be a winner either way!  If you decide you can't live without them both, we wouldn't blame you: just convo us and we can get you a combined shipping quote, no worries.
There is one main large zippered compartment with a small zippered pocket inside, one front zippered pocket, and one back open pocket.  Perfect for all your carry on, overnight travel, or commuting needs, this sturdy and attractive bag is larger than most of the high quality bags Samsonite manufactured in the 70s, and can serve you in a variety of fabulous ways.
The fabulous faux leather of this bag is complemented by the matching vinyl piping found on all the edges that helps to protect the bag.  The pinky red bag has a pleather look to it (faux leather) with a hint of light pink mixed in with the strawberry red shade, and the orange bag features more of a snakeskin texture with a bit of yellow throughout.  LOVE the mottled depth and texture on both exteriors - so rich!  
Tons of real stitching throughout the exterior will keep your bag in good shape for a long time to come, and, incredibly enough - despite being 40 years old - there is not a stitch missing anywhere!  The quality of this bag is demonstrated further by the reinforced straps and additional stitching found on the smaller sides of the bag.  
There is very little sign of wear on this super useful and cool retro vegan friendly bag.  There are a few scuffs on the vinyl exterior, including a few signs of age beginning on the metal hardware, although most parts positively shine with the bright silver chrome accents that are like "jewelry" for the bag!  The interior does show wear and has a bit of "old suitcase" smell, including wrinkles, light stains, and a few minor places where the vinyl is coming away or splitting, but nothing that should affect function much, if at all.  This bag has a ton of life in it yet and can't wait to accompany you on your next travel adventure!
It can be difficult to find one of these fantastic quality Samsonite Silhouette carry on bags from the 70s in such fabulous shades as these are.  What a cool, retro messenger bag for you to carry your laptop or iPad in!  Given as a gift, we have no doubt that your recipient, if they truly appreciate vintage and love bags, would be absolutely delighted and ever grateful for your amazing taste and incredible thoughtfulness.
All hardware is working smoothly, fully functional (minus the key for the zipper lock), done in an attractive and eye-catching silver chrome tone.  Love the chrome Samsonite badging on one side of the bag -- so very retro and eye-catching!  All compartments are lined with a practical vinyl like material, and the very bottom inside of the bag features adorable tone-on-tone matching polka dots!  The bag is nicely stabilized upright when you set it down with a very sturdy bottom that has four shiny chrome feet on the very bottom of the bag.  The bag features double straps attached with metal hardware, and includes extra strap length and reinforcement down to the bottom of each side of the bag to stabilize your heavier loads.  We think this also offers a bit of extra special style!  (So, can you tell that the more I study this bag to describe it to you, the more I want to keep it?!)  
So, where would you like to be swept off to that requires a fabulous vintage bag to help you get there?  You provide the destination and we've got the perfect vintage carry-on bag for you.
Approx. 14-1/2"  x  12-1/2"  x  6"
*We have plenty more photos we can send you if you like; just contact us and ask!
**Say, are you thinking about other goodies from our shop?  We don't blame you.  Just contact us to let us know what else and we may be able to fit them inside this bag for you for very little extra shipping charges.  We'll be more than happy to get you a custom quote!

Product name: Antique Penny Dreadful Valentine
Description:
Antique Penny Dreadful or "Vinegar" Valentine
Wonderful early Vinegar Valentine or insult card from the late 19th C. 
Penny dreadfuls were usually decorated with a caricature and (below it) an insulting verse.  They were produced in America as early as 1850.  Some were produced by such prestigious publishing houses like McLoughlin, Tuck, etc.  This one is signed " Made in US Amer"
The subjects were, more often than not, of people with animals being a bit more scarce.
This one of a cat is quite well done and wonderful.  Measuring 10 by 7 1/2 inches, it is in very good condition with fold lines attendant with age and use.  
I've always loved this one for its "charming" cat and verse (however, being a cat lover , I can honestly say I've not met too many a cat to fit that description).  But the best thing about this one is the inscription on the back :
              "To Miss Hess
                                from Lawrence Healy"
Probably Lawrence, a student, gave this to his teacher, Miss Hess on Valentine's Day.  Would you have loved to have been a fly on the wall in that classroom when she read it?

Product name: Attar of Roses Bath Oil,  4oz fragrant bath oil of roses and sandalwood, inspired by ancient India with skin loving organic grapeseed oil
Description:
Character: Sensual, aphrodisiac, youthful
Notes: Victorian Rose, Sandalwood
Skin Benefits: A combination of four skin-loving oils leave your skin moisturized and nourished.
Originating in 16th century India, this classic fragrance was first devised at the wedding feast of a famous Mogul Emperor. As the young newlyweds took a celebratory boat ride in a moat filled with rose petals, the bride noticed a fragrant oil had formed on the surface of the water. To capture the essence of this fateful day, the Emperor ordered the oil bottled in a base of sandalwood oil, a combination that became a staple in Indian households for centuries. True to its origins, this oil fuses the ancient fragrances of rose and sandalwood.
With a light fragrance concentration, like an eau de toilette, this bath oil will leave you with a subtle fragrance, perceivable by those that are close enough to brush against the skin. A truly relaxing and luxurious pleasure. The oil base includes:
Sweet Almond Oil- Rich in Vitamins E,A, and D, Sweet Almond Oil traps moisture in the skin, leaving it glowing all day.
Rice Bran Oil- A super antioxidant oil, with Vitamins E and B, which help increase elasticity and reduce the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles.
Jojoba Oil- Similar to the natural oil produced by the human body, Jojoba gently heals wounds and helps fade scars over time.
Grapeseed Oil- Light, non-greasy Grapeseed Oil is packed with skin-brightening Vitamin C. 
Not sure which fragrance is for you? Try our fragrance quiz: http://www.herbandroot.com/category-s/1872.htm

https://www.etsy.com/listing/267847608/personalize-your-bag-with-initials-name
We'd love to personalize the laptop sleeve with gold, silver or blind (no color) embossed initials. Please leave the personalization details in the notes to your order and make sure to list the initials the way you want them to appear on the product. Our font is all capital letters of the same size and the signs " " (space), "&" (and) and "." (period). We don't currently offer numerical embossing.
PLEASE NOTE: The monogram will be placed on the flap. The card holder will be stamped with our collection name ERA81.
*****SPECIAL OFFER*****
Order two and get 10% off with the code "TWOISBETTER"
*****QUALITY GUARANTEE*****
We take pride in the quality of our products. If you believe your product has or develops any defects in the craftsmanship, please contact us with the photos of the defect, and we will repair the defect at no extra cost, provided the return shipping to our studio is paid by the customer. Please note that the guarantee only covers our craftsmanship; any damage caused by improper use or care, accidents or normal wear and tear is not included.
***** SHIPPING & RETURNS *****
Ready to ship in 1 business day!
We accept returns without asking questions, just contact us within 3 days of the product delivery. Please note that customized products are not eligible for returns. 
*****OUR MATERIALS*****
We use premium full grain vegetable tanned leather to make our laptop sleeves, which is the leather that is tanned using non-toxic organic barks and leaves over a period of 30 to 40 days (unlike fast-made low-cost chrome tanned leathers that are harmful to health and environment). We source our leather from a reputable US based tannery that focuses on sustainable leather production. Vegetable tanned leather has natural color and earthy sweet smell, and develops a gorgeous patina with time preserving the story of its owner and making each piece truly unique. This means no two laptop sleeves made by us will be exactly the same!
Vegetable tanned leather, w​ith the right feeding & care,​ ​also has the ability to heal ​scratches (unlike chrome tanned leathers, which, once scratched, cannot be repaired without re-tanning). This ability makes veg tanned leather products much more durable than any chemically tanned leather goods, and keeps them presentable and rich looking for years.
***** ABOUT US *****
We nourish simplicity and elegance in our designs. Mix stunning textures, subtle geometry of shapes, warm loving craftsmanship infused with patience and attention to detail – and that is how our bags are born. Every bag is carefully cut and made by hand in our little art studio, surrounded by Californian sunlight, music, smell of coffee and refreshing greens of our ficus tree. 
Each product is gift wrapped with love and care and shipped promptly around the world. We are available at any time (apart from sleeping!) to answer your questions and help you make the right choice.

Product name: Make your own  cheese with natural rennet 100ml.
Description:
Don't you wish you could eat your own cheese everyday? Here is your chance! This rennet is suitable for any kind of cheese like mozzarella or feta cheese.
If you need rennet for large quantities of milk check here! 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/386056970/make-your-own-cheese-with-natural-rennet?ref=shop_home_active_8
Here is a recipe for feta cheese!
What we need:
2 liters of milk (sheep, goat or cow)
1/2 tsp rennet liquid 
salt
whey from the milk itself
1 cheesecloth or tulle tightly woven
Warm the milk
Dissolve the rennet in the milk
Leave about 15 minutes to thicken milk
With a spoon cut the mixture at four
Empty in cheesecloth that you settle down in pot
Let it drain 1- 1 1/2 hours.
Season with salt and keep in the refrigerator a quantity of whey
Unwrap cheese tulle,  cut vertically into two pieces and salt
Put in a bowl in the fridge with the whey will continue to drip
If it doesn't cover it, pour some more whey
The more it is left in the fridge the more it will harden
If you repeat the process, add your new cheese in the same bowl and always cover with salted whey.
You can start eating your feta cheece in 20 days! Or by the first day, but it will be soft.

The company that started Swank has actually been around since 1897, and Swank has been making jewelry and accessories since their earliest days, under different names. In 1908, they expanded their line of women’s jewelry, offering men’s jewelry and so began their reputation for cufflinks and tie related jewelry.  
While the company has been making jewelry since the early 1900’s, the name Swank was not used until the late 1920’s and most jewelry you find these days that is clearly marked as Swank will be from the 50’s or 60’s. Product name: Mystic Topaz Vintage Filigree Antique 925 Fine S0LID Sterling Silver Men's / Unisex CUFFLINKS k284
Description:
Concept: The cufflinks are casted out of Solid Fine sterling silver (Nickel Free). Great care was taken to hand layer the filigree vintage pattern enclosing each stone. The flexible posts are casted out of silver as well. Antique polish was applied to the entire outer layer to preserve and showcase its vintage texture.  
As an introductory launch into Men's line of Jewelry, I have marked these cufflinks to the bare minimum cost (includes anti tarnish case) to allow my clients to enjoy a whole new paradigm of sleek cuff links with versatile appeal for a lesser value. 
Craftsmanship: I wanted to do something bit more creative than what was done / is being already offered regarding men's cufflinks. To start at the very beginning, I decided to buy rough rocks straight from local mines/ suppliers by the lbs to procure the cabs in the exact shape and size necessary to begin my journey. Next step, was to use variety of vintage, contemporary and unique patterns to totally enclose the stone with silver (avoid the latch/prong setting) which gives the cufflinks  more depth and durability. 
Price & Affordability: Considering the large varieties of gemstones used in the cufflinks, I wanted to keep the price barrier at a lower point. One way to accomplish this is to cut the cabs from the rough rocks directly, which eliminates the need for a middleman. Secondly this gives me larger control/flexibility over the quality and pattern of cabs that can be extracted.
 ►Why buy my cufflinks over the ones available in the market? 
■ The answer to that is quite simple. I concentrate my effort on gemstones primarily, which allows me to offer my customers with a product that is authentic and high end from the Get-go. Even if you were to go buy cabs of this quality, it is going to cost you quite a bit. Lots of time and effort is spent on the craftsmanship of each of these cufflinks. Unlink most cufflinks available, these are "not" DIY project where you stick a pre-made plastic or metal frame to a post. It is a prolonged procedure from start to finish.

Description:

THIS IS NOT A FINISHED CARDIGAN. THIS IS AN INSTANT DOWNLOAD PATTERN AFTER PURCHASE. You will not be receiving a cardigan in the mail. Failure to read item descriptions indicating that this is a pattern will not result in refunds. 
You may not reproduce or claim this or any variations of this pattern as your own. However, you MAY sell any finished products created as a result of following this pattern. Please credit this shop (Calou Shop) as the pattern creator when selling your finished items. See pattern download for full rights. 
NOTES BEFORE BUYING:
I consider this an intermediate pattern. Crocheters with general knowledge of building knit garments should find this to be a straightforward pattern that is easy to adjust and customize.  
There are no stitch tutorials within the pattern for the following stitches: 
- single crochet, 
- half double crochet/crocheting in back loops of hdc,  
- slip stitch, 
- chaining, and 
- yarning over. 
Stitches and techniques that are covered with tutorials within the pattern are: 
- glover stitch/glover cluster and 
- joining ribbing to a garment as you create the ribbing. 
Please reference the last listing photo for sizing and measurements. I size this cardigan as a roomy medium, traditional large and slim extra large. I also offer in-pattern guidance on where and how to adjust the cardigan to your needs. 
Pattern and sizing is written in US terms and calls for approximately 2000 yards of a silky medium weight yarn, (i.e. Caron Simply Soft, Bernat Satin, Red Heart Soft).
PATTERN FEATURES INCLUDE:
- clear and conversational pattern instructions, minimal jargon and abbreviations. 
- full color, photo tutorials regarding complicated stitching and techniques.
- alteration points so you can adjust the pattern to fit your body perfectly.
- shop support while working through pattern, if needed!
